Key Match Events: Nathaniel Lowe hit a two-run home run against the Los Angeles Angels in the first inning.
Marcus Semien hit a leadoff home run in Sunday's win.
Josh Jung and Josh Smith both had big hits in the series with the Los Angeles Angels, where the Rangers took three of the four games.
Post-Match Reflections: Pitcher Andrew Heaney noted that his teammates are playing 'loose and free' for the final month.
Manager Bruce Bochy remarked that the team is fighting for every run and praised their resilience.
Josh Smith highlighted the impact of Josh Jung's return from injury on the team's performance.
Marcus Semien commented on how scoring runs and hitting home runs helps to loosen up the team.
